description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an Occupational Therapist to join our specialist palliative care team at The Macmillan unit , Christchurch site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will support patients with life limiting conditions to manage their symptoms, carry out activities that matter to them, facilitate preferred place of care where this is home , optimise function and quality of life goals, avoid admission where possible and offer palliative rehabilitation , carers support , complex moving and handling advise , anxiety , breathlessness and fatigue management whilst also supporting the adjustment to potential loss of roles, control and independence . Advanced communication skills , a compassionate and holistic approach , team spirit and emotional resilience are essential attributes for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be based at The Macmillan unit and cover the 16 bedded hospice plus manage a busy and clinical diverse community caseload with support of an expert , friendly and supportive MDT .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust have now merged into the University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 26th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kirsten Holt / Nicky Pateman Team Leader Therapies / Clinical Specialist Physiotherapist - - Email Macmillan.Therapy@uhd.nhs.uk - Telephone 0300 019 5322&lt;/p&gt;
